Peanut Butter Bars

1/4 c.- crunchy peanut butter
1/4 c.- honey
1 1/2 c.- oats
1/3 c.- rasins
1 tbsp- stoneground whole wheat flour

Put peanut butter and honey in saucepan and heat very gently until melted, about 4 minutes.
Add oats, rasins, and flour. Stir well until throughly mixed and the mixture has consistansy of crumbs.
Pour mix into, non-stick 6 by 9 inch, baking pan and press in with the back of spoon. Bake in a preheated oven at 375 degrees for 15 minutes.
When done, leave pan to cool, until completely cold before removing bars from pan.

The bars can be stored in air tight containers for up to 2 weeks. Makes 8 bars.
